2.00	Politzerization	Politzerization	Politzerization, also called the Politzer maneuver or method, is a medical procedure that involves inflating the middle ear by blowing air up the nose during the act of swallowing. It is often performed to reopen the Eustachian tube and equalise pressure in the sinuses.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/c/c7/Politzerization2.JPG/250px-Politzerization2.JPG
